column2: AgEagle Aerial Systems, Inc. engages in the design, distribution and support of unmanned aerial vehicle data acquisition drones for precision agriculture industry. The company is headquartered in Neodesha, Kansas and currently employs 29 full-time employees. The firm distributes its UAVs to the precision agriculture industry. The company designs and develops its drones with a focus to provide actionable data to the precision agriculture industry. The Companyâ€™s principal product is RX-60. RX-60 is an image processing UAV that is integrated with specialty precision agriculture software. The company processes and delivers geo-referenced aerial maps to desktops or tablets through the cloud. The resulted zone maps are used in Raven computers to precisely apply nutrients and chemicals to fields. The firm develops RX-60 under a private label and purchase agreement with Raven Industries, Inc. (Raven). Through the private label, Raven distributes RX-60 to the agriculture markets.
